headline: TER Q3 Deep Dive: AI Demand Drives Upside, New CFO Announced
summary: Semiconductor testing company Teradyne (NASDAQ:TER) reported Q3 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 4.3% year on year to $769.2 million. On top of that, next quarter’s revenue guidance ($960 million at the midpoint) was surprisingly good and 17.1% above what analysts were expecting. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.85 per share was 7.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
